    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is accepted based on regulatory precedent for single-condition ASTM F1717 validation and the standardized nature of the test protocol. All primary QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% acceptance criteria. The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible for its intended use in the regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
